					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Speaking of 6502 tricks, I just figured out how many times I had to do 4 consecutive ASL A or LSR A, so I just made 2 routine that does them and return, and call them, saving one byte everytime this trick is used. I was able to save about 30 bytes doing that, which is great.</div>
<br />
<br />I was thinking about a trick to do divisions by 16/multiplications by 16. If you wanted to save about 3 cycles, you could do something like this:
<br />
<br /> ldx SomeVariable
<br /> lda Table,x
<br />
<br />Table:
<br /> .db $00,$10,$20,$30,$40,$50,$60,$70,$80,$90,$A0,$B0,$C0,$D0,$E0,$F0
<br />
<br />That would be good for needing to multiply 4-bit values by 16. But you could make a 256-byte table that holds those values every $10 bytes, so you could multiply 4-bit values by 16 and save 3 cycles. The same could be applied for dividing, but it would pretty much require a 256-byte table. while it's a huge waste of ROM, it may end up saving you a scanline or two from the very frequent divisions/multiplications of 16.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/" class="postlink">-Owner of Poultry Games</a></div>
